snippet.title: A WEEK IN PARIS | travel vlog
snippet.description:
Come along on a week in Paris with me! I meant to post this a little while ago but I literally just moved to NYC yesterday so I'm a bit behind on all my content right now. Paris was such a dream to enjoy with my family and friends! I lived in Paris on my own when I was 18/19 so it was so amazing to get to show off my favorite spots to some of my favorite people. We didn't hit many of the main touristy spots because most of us had done them before and wanted to just enjoy every day life in the city. 
with love, 
elena

replies.textDisplay: Ikram Yagoub I feel like it’s because so many movies and books romanticise Paris. Everyone talks about it like it’s a magical place while it’s just a normal city. I mean it’s beautiful but it’s a city. But because it was so important in the past they talk about it like it’s special. Lately I even discovered that the  “Paris syndrome” exists and it’s basically when people come to Paris expecting it to be the most wonderful thing they’ve ever seen and then its just a city and they’re so disappointed that they are in shock. It’s so weird!
